source.name: Marine Geophysical Data Viewer
source.description: This interactive map displays ship tracks from the Marine Trackline Geophysics database at NOAA's National Geophysical Data Center, which contains bathymetry, magnetics, gravity and seismic navigation data collected during marine cruises from 1939 to the present. Coverage is worldwide. Data sources include both US and foreign oceanographic institutions and government agencies. The map is available in a global (Mercator) projection as well as an Arctic projection.
